content:
I am trying to run a Python script from a '.py' file in a Google Colab notebook. Initially, I tried executing the following code: 
```javascript
%%javascript
IPython.OutputArea.prototype._should_scroll = function(lines) {
    return false;
}

%run rl_base.py
```
However, I received an error stating that the 'rl_base.py' file was not found. I have already uploaded the file to Google Drive and am trying to run my '.ipynb' file, which contains the above code, from the same folder. How can I correctly run this Python script in my notebook?
